## Using Legendary Techniques

### Building to Momentum +6

Reaching +6 Momentum requires sustained success:

**Aggressive Stance:** 6 successful attacks (generates +1 per hit)
**Balanced Stance:** 6 excellent rolls of 10+ (generates +1 per excellence)
**Defensive Stance:** Being attacked 6 times (generates +1 per targeting)

Alternatively, combine Momentum generation with Momentum preservation—generate +3, spend none, generate +3 more.

Party coordination accelerates: allies grant Momentum through support actions, healing, or buffs.

### Maximizing Impact

Legendary techniques should resolve situations, not just contribute:

**Don't waste on minor enemies:** Save for climactic confrontations
**Don't activate early:** Build to +6 later in fight when enemies worn down
**Don't use without setup:** Coordinate party to maximize legendary technique impact

When you activate legendary technique, it should feel like the moment the battle turned.

### Narrative Weight

Legendary techniques deserve description:

*"Standard attack":* "You hit for 15 damage."

*"Legendary technique":* "You've built Momentum through perfect combat—each successful strike accumulates power crackling around you. Now facing the dragon at last, you channel everything into single perfect strike. Unstoppable Assault activates—reality itself cannot prevent your blade from finding the dragon's heart. Maximum damage, perfect accuracy, the impossible made inevitable."

Game Masters should encourage players to describe legendary technique activations dramatically.

